WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.032 --> 00:00:01.579
Previously on <i>Siren...</i>

2
00:00:01.604 --> 00:00:02.622
<i>Bring it in!</i>

3
00:00:02.647 --> 00:00:03.946
We caught something out there.

4
00:00:04.020 --> 00:00:06.021
It attacked Chris.
He had to get airlifted out.

5
00:00:06.055 --> 00:00:08.118
Big-ass military commando helicopter.

6
00:00:08.145 --> 00:00:09.767
<i>You really don't know
what attacked him?</i>

7
00:00:09.792 --> 00:00:11.000
This was a predator.

8
00:00:11.025 --> 00:00:13.004
150 years ago.

9
00:00:13.029 --> 00:00:15.747
a local fishing captain
fell in love with a mermaid

10
00:00:15.780 --> 00:00:17.214
<i>in these very waters.</i>

11
00:00:17.288 --> 00:00:19.023
Had a report six weeks ago.

12
00:00:19.050 --> 00:00:21.561
Japanese fisherman claimed
he saw a sea creature.

13
00:00:21.586 --> 00:00:22.649
<i>We knew something was out there.</i>

14
00:00:22.673 --> 00:00:23.787
<i>That's when I alerted your people.</i>

15
00:00:23.811 --> 00:00:24.947
You okay?

16
00:00:24.972 --> 00:00:27.187
Little girl runnin' away from home.

17
00:00:30.671 --> 00:00:32.138
You're sick. Can I see?

18
00:00:32.299 --> 00:00:33.778
Oh. Hey.

19
00:00:33.860 --> 00:00:35.584
This is Ryn. I don't
think she speaks English.

20
00:00:38.365 --> 00:00:41.472
Your ancestors slaughtered
those beautiful creatures.

21
00:00:41.504 --> 00:00:44.139
Genocide... that's your legacy.

22
00:00:44.224 --> 00:00:45.582
Hey. we got somethin'.

23
00:00:45.640 --> 00:00:47.307
Wow. that's big.

24
00:00:47.721 --> 00:00:49.122
Whoa. whoa. look.

25
00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:57.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

26
00:01:03.370 --> 00:01:04.570
- Stop! Don't!
- Aah!

27
00:01:04.595 --> 00:01:05.996
What the hell?!

28
00:01:06.212 --> 00:01:07.896
You don't want to do that.
That could kill it.

29
00:01:07.921 --> 00:01:09.233
Thought you said you came
out here to help us.

30
00:01:09.257 --> 00:01:11.892
I had a clean shot till you stepped in.

31
00:01:11.972 --> 00:01:14.040
Almost like you don't
want us catching it.

32
00:01:14.994 --> 00:01:17.423
Look. if this thing really is
what you think it is.

33
00:01:17.458 --> 00:01:19.592
we need to protect it. not kill it.

34
00:01:19.626 --> 00:01:21.294
Ugh!

35
00:01:21.720 --> 00:01:23.596
We want what belongs to us.

36
00:01:23.850 --> 00:01:25.415
and we want to get Chris back.

37
00:01:25.476 --> 00:01:26.788
If you don't want the same thing.

38
00:01:26.813 --> 00:01:28.036
I don't know what the hell
you're doing on the boat.

39
00:01:28.060 --> 00:01:29.749
Shh. shh!

40
00:01:30.777 --> 00:01:32.177
Hear that?

41
00:01:36.490 --> 00:01:39.261
It's like. I don't know. it's injured?

42
00:01:43.196 --> 00:01:44.796
Maybe I hit it.

43
00:01:47.688 --> 00:01:48.921
It's underneath.

44
00:01:49.156 --> 00:01:51.624
- It's underneath the boat!
- We gotta get it.

45
00:01:53.647 --> 00:01:54.948
Ben!

46
00:01:56.076 --> 00:01:57.309
- Ben!
- Ben!

47
00:02:04.845 --> 00:02:06.305
- Ben!
- Ben!

48
00:02:28.562 --> 00:02:29.782
Come on!

49
00:02:30.984 --> 00:02:32.289
Ben!

50
00:02:32.900 --> 00:02:35.135
- What the...
- What the hell is that?

51
00:02:36.879 --> 00:02:38.480
Ben! Ben. come on!

52
00:02:38.678 --> 00:02:40.379
Get over here.

53
00:03:25.413 --> 00:03:27.789
It might be a Doppler current profiler.

54
00:03:28.189 --> 00:03:30.643
Oceanographers uses them
to study current patterns.

55
00:03:30.763 --> 00:03:31.963
When we had the creature in the hold.

56
00:03:31.988 --> 00:03:34.089
it... it made a sound.

57
00:03:34.180 --> 00:03:36.281
not too different
from the sound this thing makes.

58
00:03:36.655 --> 00:03:38.108
Right.

59
00:03:38.191 --> 00:03:40.645
Well. there's a lot of scientific

60
00:03:40.670 --> 00:03:42.552
monitoring devices floating out there.

61
00:03:42.816 --> 00:03:43.949
Could be a lot of things.

62
00:03:43.974 --> 00:03:45.580
Well. just think about it.

63
00:03:45.732 --> 00:03:47.366
We were out here. what.
like. a few days ago?

64
00:03:47.391 --> 00:03:48.486
And this thing wasn't here.

65
00:03:48.511 --> 00:03:49.517
And then we catch that creature.

66
00:03:49.541 --> 00:03:50.720
and. all of a sudden. it just appears?

67
00:03:50.744 --> 00:03:52.711
Somebody put it here.
It's gotta be connected.

68
00:03:52.746 --> 00:03:54.447
Yeah. you could be right.

69
00:03:59.504 --> 00:04:01.067
You know. that was. um...

70
00:04:01.154 --> 00:04:03.123
That was a pretty sick thing
you did back there.

71
00:04:03.148 --> 00:04:04.590
diving in like that.

72
00:04:04.843 --> 00:04:07.260
Yeah. Well. it seemed
like a good idea at the time.

73
00:04:08.417 --> 00:04:10.429
Look. I'm sorry.

74
00:04:10.464 --> 00:04:12.361
okay. if I pissed you off earlier.

75
00:04:12.432 --> 00:04:14.633
I just feel differently
about it than you guys.

76
00:04:14.735 --> 00:04:17.203
It doesn't mean that I
don't want to find Chris.

77
00:04:18.510 --> 00:04:19.943
I appreciate it.

78
00:04:21.036 --> 00:04:22.278
For real.

79
00:04:22.363 --> 00:04:23.930
Couldn't tell.

80
00:04:23.967 --> 00:04:26.061
'cause you were being
such a dick about it.

81
00:04:30.691 --> 00:04:31.891
What is it?

82
00:04:34.057 --> 00:04:37.025
I don't know. This thing
looks like a camera.

83
00:04:37.350 --> 00:04:39.692
There's probably some kind
of tracking device on it. too.

84
00:04:39.717 --> 00:04:40.905
We should try to disable it.

85
00:04:40.930 --> 00:04:42.802
I say we just power it up
and set it off.

86
00:04:42.882 --> 00:04:44.983
Let the military come.
They'll lead us to Chris.

87
00:04:45.008 --> 00:04:46.332
and maybe they got the mermaid. too.

88
00:04:46.379 --> 00:04:47.725
I wouldn't.

89
00:04:48.729 --> 00:04:50.980
You saw what happened
the last time they came.

90
00:04:51.180 --> 00:04:52.701
We could all end up like Chris.

91
00:04:52.726 --> 00:04:55.395
We just need to take our time

92
00:04:55.869 --> 00:04:58.704
and try to figure out
what this thing really is.

93
00:05:00.132 --> 00:05:02.133
Okay.

94
00:05:34.434 --> 00:05:36.343
Take your sister inside the house!

95
00:05:57.978 --> 00:06:00.598
Hey! What the hell are you doin'?

96
00:06:00.745 --> 00:06:02.875
Takin' my clothes?

97
00:06:02.957 --> 00:06:04.835
I am sick of you little junkies
comin' around here

98
00:06:04.860 --> 00:06:06.448
messin' with my stuff.

99
00:06:06.993 --> 00:06:09.994
Don't you threaten me.

100
00:07:03.904 --> 00:07:05.824
<i>Hey. it's Ben. Leave me a message.</i>

101
00:07:07.008 --> 00:07:08.742
Hey. it's me.

102
00:07:09.003 --> 00:07:10.503
I'm getting worried about you.

103
00:07:10.616 --> 00:07:13.719
Give me a call.
Let me know you're okay.

104
00:07:33.819 --> 00:07:35.318
Hello?

105
00:07:49.514 --> 00:07:50.993
You get a hold of CSI?

106
00:07:51.018 --> 00:07:53.784
Comin' from Port Angeles.
Should be here soon.

107
00:07:56.635 --> 00:07:58.158
What do you got. Clarence?

108
00:07:58.183 --> 00:07:59.915
That is Donnie Price.

109
00:08:00.401 --> 00:08:01.832
He's got some priors.

110
00:08:01.881 --> 00:08:04.846
Aggravated assault.
drunk and disorderly.

111
00:08:04.928 --> 00:08:06.329
Pants are ridin' a little low.

112
00:08:06.369 --> 00:08:08.234
Possible sexual assault?

113
00:08:08.355 --> 00:08:10.369
Looks like he got what he deserved.

114
00:08:10.541 --> 00:08:13.408
Or there was a third person
in the car with them.

115
00:08:13.522 --> 00:08:15.554
Somebody came up on them.

116
00:08:18.356 --> 00:08:21.873
Whoever did this was of
substantial size and strength.

117
00:08:22.249 --> 00:08:23.672
Start lookin' around.

118
00:09:07.283 --> 00:09:09.082
How much for this?

119
00:09:09.289 --> 00:09:12.460
I'm. uh. very sorry. Shop's closed.

120
00:09:12.597 --> 00:09:13.995
Come back another day. huh?

121
00:09:14.089 --> 00:09:15.503
Thank you.

122
00:09:29.783 --> 00:09:31.282
You came back.

123
00:09:37.524 --> 00:09:39.290
Why are you here?

124
00:10:14.958 --> 00:10:16.389
I...

125
00:10:20.925 --> 00:10:22.591
See?

126
00:10:33.485 --> 00:10:34.783
Look?

127
00:10:35.892 --> 00:10:37.820
You look.

128
00:10:43.825 --> 00:10:44.990
Ryn.

129
00:10:45.465 --> 00:10:47.164
Ryn.

130
00:10:47.379 --> 00:10:48.864
That's you.

131
00:10:58.765 --> 00:10:59.931
Look.

132
00:11:03.351 --> 00:11:04.836
There's another one?

133
00:11:11.679 --> 00:11:13.611
30 ccs of spinal fluid.

134
00:11:14.160 --> 00:11:16.844
and take tissue core samples
from the upper thoracic region.

135
00:11:17.032 --> 00:11:18.731
How many?

136
00:11:20.026 --> 00:11:21.437
Take six for now.

137
00:11:21.472 --> 00:11:22.670
I'll order more as needed.

138
00:11:22.732 --> 00:11:23.964
How are the other tests going?

139
00:11:23.989 --> 00:11:25.746
- Very well.
- We're ready for extraction?

140
00:12:06.207 --> 00:12:07.506
I got your text.

141
00:12:07.719 --> 00:12:09.604
Where the hell have you been?

142
00:12:12.121 --> 00:12:13.720
What's wrong?

143
00:12:19.467 --> 00:12:20.880
Whoa!

144
00:12:20.981 --> 00:12:22.946
What happened? Are you okay?

145
00:12:24.412 --> 00:12:25.951
It's not what you're thinking.

146
00:12:26.040 --> 00:12:28.339
How do you know what I'm thinking?

147
00:12:28.614 --> 00:12:31.457
'Cause it literally couldn't be
anything that you're thinking.

148
00:12:32.561 --> 00:12:34.268
I gotta show you something.

149
00:12:39.321 --> 00:12:41.214
- Yo. man.
- Yo.

150
00:12:44.488 --> 00:12:45.754
What is that?

151
00:12:45.779 --> 00:12:47.649
We found it out in the water.

152
00:12:47.674 --> 00:12:48.930
It was making this...

153
00:12:48.995 --> 00:12:50.861
I don't know. this weird-ass sound.

154
00:12:51.561 --> 00:12:53.244
Ben said we should take our time.

155
00:12:53.321 --> 00:12:54.622
try to figure out who's runnin' it.

156
00:12:54.673 --> 00:12:55.820
what they're up to.

157
00:12:55.867 --> 00:12:57.246
Wait. Ben knows about this?

158
00:12:57.282 --> 00:12:58.515
Yeah. he came out with us.

159
00:12:58.549 --> 00:13:00.248
And now he's telling us what to do?

160
00:13:00.729 --> 00:13:02.142
Don't trust him. man.

161
00:13:02.167 --> 00:13:03.767
The guy crewed up with us
for a few seasons.

162
00:13:03.792 --> 00:13:05.268
but he was always
just slumming it until college.

163
00:13:05.292 --> 00:13:06.669
- You know that. right?
- Yeah. but. I mean.

164
00:13:06.693 --> 00:13:08.058
you guys were never close. all right?

165
00:13:08.083 --> 00:13:09.464
I been through a lot with him.

166
00:13:09.643 --> 00:13:11.857
I hear you. but look at his family.

167
00:13:12.431 --> 00:13:14.104
He's not one of us. man.

168
00:13:14.249 --> 00:13:15.782
Never has been.

169
00:13:27.003 --> 00:13:28.829
It has to be here.

170
00:13:33.376 --> 00:13:34.658
All I see are sea lions.

171
00:13:34.722 --> 00:13:35.854
It'll be here.

172
00:13:36.302 --> 00:13:37.555
There!

173
00:13:37.622 --> 00:13:38.954
Look.

174
00:13:47.423 --> 00:13:49.586
I went in to save her.

175
00:13:49.908 --> 00:13:51.558
And then she turned into that

176
00:13:51.583 --> 00:13:53.382
and attacked me.

177
00:13:53.885 --> 00:13:55.737
- Maddie?
- Play it again.

178
00:13:56.777 --> 00:13:58.089
Okay.

179
00:13:58.242 --> 00:14:00.077
Here's a different camera.

180
00:14:06.496 --> 00:14:08.462
Oh. man.

181
00:14:08.542 --> 00:14:10.508
This is real.

182
00:14:11.030 --> 00:14:13.395
Maddie. this is really happening.

183
00:14:14.575 --> 00:14:16.301
I'm sorry I didn't believe you.

184
00:14:16.377 --> 00:14:18.542
It's kinda hard to believe someone

185
00:14:18.567 --> 00:14:19.747
when they tell you they just saw...

186
00:14:19.772 --> 00:14:21.339
Mermaid.

187
00:14:21.470 --> 00:14:23.135
Yeah.

188
00:14:43.781 --> 00:14:44.903
Okay. I got...

189
00:14:44.935 --> 00:14:46.501
Aah!

190
00:14:48.791 --> 00:14:50.241
It's me.

191
00:14:51.101 --> 00:14:52.466
Helen.

192
00:14:52.721 --> 00:14:54.053
Helen.

193
00:14:57.521 --> 00:14:59.087
Helen.

194
00:15:02.411 --> 00:15:04.708
Hello. Helen.

195
00:15:06.134 --> 00:15:07.984
You learn quickly.

196
00:15:10.441 --> 00:15:12.777
<i>Oh. thank you. Lord...</i>

197
00:15:12.921 --> 00:15:14.749
That's my neighbor's book.

198
00:15:17.942 --> 00:15:19.474
Two girls.

199
00:15:25.869 --> 00:15:27.334
"Sister."

200
00:15:29.249 --> 00:15:30.982
Sisters.

201
00:15:34.355 --> 00:15:36.888
Is that who you're looking for?

202
00:15:37.428 --> 00:15:39.361
For your sister?

203
00:15:40.562 --> 00:15:42.062
Sister.

204
00:15:44.595 --> 00:15:46.095
I'll be damned.

205
00:15:48.669 --> 00:15:51.002
I have these for you.

206
00:15:52.502 --> 00:15:53.668
Put them on.

207
00:16:09.476 --> 00:16:11.675
Oh. Lovely.

208
00:16:18.003 --> 00:16:19.779
You need food.

209
00:16:19.910 --> 00:16:23.175
Humans love to eat.

210
00:16:24.871 --> 00:16:26.436
We do most of our hunting

211
00:16:26.461 --> 00:16:28.094
in a supermarket.

212
00:16:37.609 --> 00:16:39.975
Oh. no. No. Uh-uh!

213
00:16:41.989 --> 00:16:44.252
Please. give.

214
00:16:44.757 --> 00:16:46.356
Give.

215
00:16:46.381 --> 00:16:47.653
Thank you.

216
00:16:47.677 --> 00:16:49.776
I think I know what you need.

217
00:16:49.857 --> 00:16:51.989
You stay here.

218
00:16:52.197 --> 00:16:54.296
I'll go get you food.

219
00:16:54.531 --> 00:16:57.329
Then we'll look for your sister.

220
00:16:57.697 --> 00:16:59.028
Okay?

221
00:17:16.564 --> 00:17:19.264
<i>There's something else. Maddie.</i>

222
00:17:19.289 --> 00:17:20.888
When I went out with Xander.

223
00:17:20.913 --> 00:17:23.346
we found this device in the water.

224
00:17:23.637 --> 00:17:26.772
Some kind of military tracking device.

225
00:17:26.797 --> 00:17:28.524
I think they're looking for her.

226
00:17:28.591 --> 00:17:31.261
The military? This is crazy.

227
00:17:32.170 --> 00:17:34.165
Does anyone else know about her?

228
00:17:34.244 --> 00:17:37.444
Uh. yeah. just the guys on the boat

229
00:17:37.469 --> 00:17:39.268
and Miss Hawkins.

230
00:17:39.318 --> 00:17:40.759
Helen Hawkins?

231
00:17:40.985 --> 00:17:42.944
You told her? Why would you do that?

232
00:17:43.038 --> 00:17:45.130
She was talking
to that girl on the street.

233
00:17:45.155 --> 00:17:47.639
I... It looked like she knew
something about her.

234
00:17:47.664 --> 00:17:48.730
so I went to talk to her.

235
00:17:48.755 --> 00:17:49.925
Well. what did she say?

236
00:17:49.950 --> 00:17:51.814
She started talking
about my family. Maddie.

237
00:17:51.839 --> 00:17:54.438
She was saying I should
ask my dad about it.

238
00:17:54.945 --> 00:17:56.232
Your dad? Well...

239
00:17:56.431 --> 00:17:58.216
Did you talk to him?

240
00:17:58.686 --> 00:18:00.819
Not yet.

241
00:18:01.398 --> 00:18:02.731
It's done.

242
00:18:02.756 --> 00:18:04.955
All the video's downloaded.

243
00:18:05.457 --> 00:18:08.445
This thing. it attacked you.

244
00:18:08.470 --> 00:18:10.090
it... it got Chris.

245
00:18:10.227 --> 00:18:11.715
It's dangerous.

246
00:18:11.846 --> 00:18:14.979
If we're gonna go after
it. try to track it down.

247
00:18:15.510 --> 00:18:17.235
we need to be careful.

248
00:18:18.252 --> 00:18:19.660
You're right.

249
00:18:23.899 --> 00:18:26.964
Dude. you know what? You were right.

250
00:18:27.159 --> 00:18:28.520
It makes sense.

251
00:18:28.580 --> 00:18:30.145
We reconnect the tracking equipment.

252
00:18:30.170 --> 00:18:31.934
we power that thing up. and
when the military comes.

253
00:18:31.959 --> 00:18:33.749
Boom! We ambush them.

254
00:18:33.774 --> 00:18:34.869
You need to calm down.

255
00:18:34.894 --> 00:18:36.652
We are not gonna ambush the military.

256
00:18:36.740 --> 00:18:38.138
- Calm down?
- Yeah.

257
00:18:38.226 --> 00:18:39.825
You sound just like Ben.

258
00:18:39.919 --> 00:18:41.892
Okay. look. you don't
know him like I do. all right?

259
00:18:41.917 --> 00:18:43.983
Look. I told you.
stop listening to him!

260
00:18:44.021 --> 00:18:45.695
He's got no clue what we're
dealing with right now.

261
00:18:45.719 --> 00:18:47.131
Pretty sure he's one of the only people

262
00:18:47.156 --> 00:18:48.240
that actually does have a clue

263
00:18:48.265 --> 00:18:49.264
what we're dealing with right now.

264
00:18:49.288 --> 00:18:51.858
so maybe you should just give
him a little faith. all right?

265
00:19:01.653 --> 00:19:03.914
That's a good run of sockeye.

266
00:19:04.014 --> 00:19:05.843
Enjoy it while it lasts.

267
00:19:05.892 --> 00:19:07.207
Yeah. I worry about that. too.

268
00:19:07.232 --> 00:19:09.061
but I also worry about people.

269
00:19:09.220 --> 00:19:11.796
And right now. I'm giving good
jobs to folks who need them.

270
00:19:11.968 --> 00:19:13.631
I wanted to ask you something.

271
00:19:14.542 --> 00:19:16.240
I remember that you and Grandpa

272
00:19:16.265 --> 00:19:17.762
used to talk about Charles Pownall.

273
00:19:17.845 --> 00:19:21.272
about what really happened back then.

274
00:19:22.480 --> 00:19:24.627
You really come here to ask me that?

275
00:19:24.741 --> 00:19:26.090
Yeah.

276
00:19:27.523 --> 00:19:29.889
Why the sudden interest
in the family history?

277
00:19:32.741 --> 00:19:33.928
I ran into Helen Hawkins.

278
00:19:33.959 --> 00:19:35.431
Oh. come on.

279
00:19:35.637 --> 00:19:37.168
Dad?

280
00:19:38.272 --> 00:19:40.967
Maybe I'd show up to more family events

281
00:19:41.021 --> 00:19:42.666
like the statue unveiling

282
00:19:42.731 --> 00:19:45.792
if you told me the real
story about our family.

283
00:19:47.470 --> 00:19:48.833
All right.

284
00:19:50.751 --> 00:19:52.106
Look...

285
00:19:52.816 --> 00:19:56.393
Charles might not have been exactly
who we make him out to be.

286
00:19:57.254 --> 00:19:58.510
I can't say for sure.

287
00:19:58.535 --> 00:20:00.387
but there might have been
some mental illness.

288
00:20:00.612 --> 00:20:02.629
maybe even schizophrenia.

289
00:20:03.414 --> 00:20:05.412
Long months at sea.
a constant stream of booze.

290
00:20:05.437 --> 00:20:08.718
and. uh. well. he was seeing things.

291
00:20:09.421 --> 00:20:11.317
Mermaids?

292
00:20:11.740 --> 00:20:14.222
You know this.
You did the play in school.

293
00:20:14.739 --> 00:20:16.236
That's how the town got its folklore.

294
00:20:16.261 --> 00:20:17.929
Now. as for Helen and her stories.

295
00:20:17.954 --> 00:20:20.216
well. we all know she's
got a vivid imagination.

296
00:20:22.785 --> 00:20:24.268
That's it?

297
00:20:24.597 --> 00:20:25.906
That's it.

298
00:20:28.863 --> 00:20:30.060
Why?

299
00:20:32.689 --> 00:20:34.786
Dad. I gotta go.

300
00:20:38.947 --> 00:20:41.752
I'll take a pound of mussels.

301
00:20:41.861 --> 00:20:44.128
Oh. and a pound of clams.

302
00:20:44.204 --> 00:20:46.508
Yeah. make sure you get the big ones.

303
00:20:46.747 --> 00:20:48.481
Shrimp... give me two dozen shrimp

304
00:20:48.506 --> 00:20:50.069
and some scallops.

305
00:20:50.096 --> 00:20:52.469
Yeah. a little bit
of that sockeye. crab.

306
00:20:52.542 --> 00:20:53.845
Actually. make that two.

307
00:20:53.870 --> 00:20:56.201
I'll take two. two crabs. Thanks. yeah.

308
00:20:56.225 --> 00:20:58.476
No. that's a baby. I'm gonna
have to get something else.

309
00:20:58.500 --> 00:21:00.586
That nice. big salmon over there?

310
00:21:00.778 --> 00:21:02.389
Thank you.

311
00:21:02.761 --> 00:21:04.491
Anything else?

312
00:21:05.191 --> 00:21:07.386
Got any sardines?

313
00:21:13.984 --> 00:21:15.747
Calvin?

314
00:21:15.854 --> 00:21:17.151
Hey. Calvin!

315
00:21:17.738 --> 00:21:18.902
Yeah?

316
00:21:19.042 --> 00:21:20.638
Did you move it?

317
00:21:20.887 --> 00:21:22.084
What. the thing? No. I didn't touch it.

318
00:21:22.108 --> 00:21:23.771
Well. it's gone.

319
00:21:27.074 --> 00:21:28.681
You see?

320
00:21:28.985 --> 00:21:30.316
See what?

321
00:21:31.955 --> 00:21:34.749
The military came and took the mermaid.

322
00:21:34.961 --> 00:21:36.317
took Chris.

323
00:21:36.377 --> 00:21:38.395
and now they came in here
and took the thing.

324
00:21:42.983 --> 00:21:44.805
We shouldn't even be
talking in here right now.

325
00:22:19.683 --> 00:22:21.113
Where am I?

326
00:22:27.524 --> 00:22:29.586
What's happening?

327
00:22:45.208 --> 00:22:46.737
They've been out here all this time.

328
00:22:46.738 --> 00:22:48.513
so why are they showing up now?

329
00:22:49.219 --> 00:22:50.363
I was thinking the same thing

330
00:22:50.387 --> 00:22:51.708
when I was at my dad's.

331
00:22:51.733 --> 00:22:52.802
What do you mean?

332
00:22:52.827 --> 00:22:54.863
Something brought her closer
to the surface. all right?

333
00:22:54.907 --> 00:22:57.368
Maybe it's the change
in the oceans. you know?

334
00:22:57.393 --> 00:22:59.206
Maybe she's looking
for a new food source.

335
00:22:59.253 --> 00:23:01.381
- Same as our sea lions.
- Right.

336
00:23:01.463 --> 00:23:02.892
Thanks to my family.

337
00:23:15.785 --> 00:23:18.413
Helen Hawkins seems to know
a lot about this stuff.

338
00:23:18.920 --> 00:23:21.082
I'm hoping she'll have some answers.

339
00:23:21.337 --> 00:23:22.627
Well. there she is.

340
00:23:22.652 --> 00:23:24.016
The town nut job.

341
00:23:25.836 --> 00:23:27.364
<i>Yeah.</i>

342
00:23:27.726 --> 00:23:30.620
Maybe don't say that in front of her.

343
00:23:36.942 --> 00:23:39.511
Oh. uh. shop's closed.

344
00:23:39.536 --> 00:23:40.761
Sorry to bother you.

345
00:23:40.785 --> 00:23:43.112
but I just had a few more
questions I wanted to ask you.

346
00:23:43.900 --> 00:23:45.769
You told her?

347
00:23:45.910 --> 00:23:48.239
Yeah. We can trust her.

348
00:23:48.639 --> 00:23:50.712
It's not about trust.

349
00:23:51.301 --> 00:23:53.331
No one else can know.

350
00:23:53.946 --> 00:23:56.312
These creatures were massacred once.

351
00:23:56.812 --> 00:23:58.070
It could happen again.

352
00:23:58.134 --> 00:24:00.686
Look. we're not
gonna tell anyone. okay?

353
00:24:00.711 --> 00:24:01.742
We want to protect them. too.

354
00:24:03.604 --> 00:24:06.573
I. uh. told you everything I know.

355
00:24:10.364 --> 00:24:11.727
She's gone.

356
00:24:11.752 --> 00:24:14.248
probably a hundred miles
out in the ocean by now.

357
00:24:22.545 --> 00:24:24.374
Is everything okay?

358
00:24:24.947 --> 00:24:27.193
Plumbing issues. It's an old building.

359
00:24:27.257 --> 00:24:29.373
I have things to do.

360
00:24:29.439 --> 00:24:30.844
so if you don't mind...

361
00:24:30.869 --> 00:24:32.965
This is just gonna take a second.

362
00:24:35.989 --> 00:24:37.618
We found this in the water.

363
00:24:37.680 --> 00:24:39.809
I was wondering if you could
tell me what this sound is.

364
00:24:50.459 --> 00:24:51.456
Turn it off.

365
00:25:04.170 --> 00:25:05.514
Aah!

366
00:25:10.425 --> 00:25:12.555
Turn it off now!

367
00:25:24.823 --> 00:25:26.187
Aah!

368
00:25:31.006 --> 00:25:32.669
Sister!

369
00:25:46.162 --> 00:25:47.963
Close it. close it!

370
00:25:51.213 --> 00:25:52.877
Sister!

371
00:25:53.337 --> 00:25:54.697
Sister!

372
00:25:54.794 --> 00:25:56.124
That sound is your sister?

373
00:25:56.631 --> 00:25:58.261
She's not in there.

374
00:25:58.475 --> 00:26:00.689
It's... It's just a recording.

375
00:26:02.402 --> 00:26:03.765
Only sound.

376
00:26:06.042 --> 00:26:07.548
Better?

377
00:26:12.699 --> 00:26:14.695
There were two of them out there.

378
00:26:14.801 --> 00:26:16.511
Her sister's the one who got caught.

379
00:26:19.069 --> 00:26:20.366
What?

380
00:26:23.355 --> 00:26:25.059
Aah!

381
00:26:29.126 --> 00:26:31.254
Aah!

382
00:26:39.607 --> 00:26:40.938
Whoa.

383
00:26:46.084 --> 00:26:47.394
Are you okay?

384
00:26:55.245 --> 00:26:57.470
Look. I get it.

385
00:26:58.620 --> 00:27:01.891
You came back
to find your sister. right?

386
00:27:04.361 --> 00:27:05.958
We can help you.

387
00:27:09.805 --> 00:27:11.835
Okay.

388
00:27:11.889 --> 00:27:12.851
Yes.

389
00:27:12.901 --> 00:27:14.264
She understands.

390
00:27:14.498 --> 00:27:16.146
They're highly intelligent.

391
00:27:16.343 --> 00:27:18.471
More so than humans.

392
00:27:23.490 --> 00:27:25.286
Okay.

393
00:27:25.445 --> 00:27:28.037
Ben. her sister could be anywhere.

394
00:27:28.110 --> 00:27:29.859
How would we find her?

395
00:27:30.672 --> 00:27:32.002
I don't know.

396
00:27:32.812 --> 00:27:34.481
We should probably start with Xander.

397
00:27:34.537 --> 00:27:36.344
I want to hear again
what happened out there.

398
00:27:36.369 --> 00:27:38.140
Maybe there's something I missed.

399
00:27:40.716 --> 00:27:41.780
Look.

400
00:27:45.387 --> 00:27:46.945
Wait. wait.

401
00:27:47.039 --> 00:27:48.235
Hey! She...

402
00:27:48.263 --> 00:27:50.292
She can't just go out into the world.

403
00:27:51.359 --> 00:27:53.454
Do we have a choice?

404
00:27:53.853 --> 00:27:56.315
Bring her back later.

405
00:27:56.490 --> 00:27:58.153
She's safe with me.

406
00:28:13.376 --> 00:28:15.197
I'm sorry.

407
00:28:15.692 --> 00:28:17.555
I'm sorry we did that to you.

408
00:28:57.537 --> 00:28:58.874
So how long did you know him?

409
00:28:59.186 --> 00:29:01.446
He moved in about eight months ago.

410
00:29:01.506 --> 00:29:03.493
- Mm-hmm.
- Liked to party.

411
00:29:03.538 --> 00:29:05.068
had a lot of girlfriends.

412
00:29:05.362 --> 00:29:06.524
Drugs.

413
00:29:06.594 --> 00:29:07.991
Uh. not a bad guy.

414
00:29:08.205 --> 00:29:09.868
but not good. either.

415
00:29:09.946 --> 00:29:11.998
Well. he's not either anymore.

416
00:29:12.246 --> 00:29:14.037
Listen. if you think of anything else.

417
00:29:14.248 --> 00:29:16.273
- give me a call. all right?
- Sheriff?

418
00:29:16.562 --> 00:29:17.524
Oh. boy.

419
00:29:17.577 --> 00:29:18.604
Phillip.

420
00:29:18.630 --> 00:29:19.781
Vicki.

421
00:29:19.855 --> 00:29:22.223
- I have a crime to report.
- Yeah?

422
00:29:22.325 --> 00:29:25.169
This little homeless girl's been
stealing clothing off my line.

423
00:29:25.233 --> 00:29:26.943
She got my daughter's
Huskies sweatshirt.

424
00:29:26.968 --> 00:29:28.669
this morning. a T-shirt.

425
00:29:29.063 --> 00:29:30.552
I went out to confront her.

426
00:29:30.577 --> 00:29:32.745
and she threw a damn metal pole at me.

427
00:29:32.915 --> 00:29:35.250
Almost took my head off.

428
00:29:35.697 --> 00:29:37.198
Is that right?

429
00:29:39.028 --> 00:29:40.562
What'd she look like?

430
00:29:55.824 --> 00:29:58.076
Xander? Hey. yeah. I've been
trying to get a hold of you.

431
00:29:58.167 --> 00:29:59.668
Where are you?

432
00:30:01.320 --> 00:30:02.681
He's at The Anchor.

433
00:30:28.140 --> 00:30:29.362
- No.
- No.

434
00:30:29.387 --> 00:30:30.994
No. no. no. no. no. no.

435
00:30:31.019 --> 00:30:32.129
Wait. wait.

436
00:30:32.154 --> 00:30:33.569
Too many people.

437
00:30:34.399 --> 00:30:36.844
It's not safe. Not safe.

438
00:30:37.655 --> 00:30:39.039
You stay here.

439
00:30:39.450 --> 00:30:41.084
I'll stay with her.

440
00:30:41.932 --> 00:30:43.395
We'll stay together.

441
00:30:43.487 --> 00:30:46.289
Then we'll... Then... Then
we'll look for your sister.

442
00:30:47.612 --> 00:30:49.107
Are you sure?

443
00:30:49.966 --> 00:30:51.233
Yeah.

444
00:30:51.641 --> 00:30:52.721
Do you wanna...

445
00:30:52.746 --> 00:30:54.575
You wanna wait outside the car?

446
00:30:55.312 --> 00:30:57.013
I'll be okay.

447
00:30:59.389 --> 00:31:01.991
All right. Be careful.

448
00:31:17.928 --> 00:31:19.134
Hi.

449
00:31:33.979 --> 00:31:35.479
Decoration.

450
00:31:36.962 --> 00:31:38.292
You like them?

451
00:31:58.203 --> 00:32:00.236
Raven feather.

452
00:32:00.738 --> 00:32:02.039
Bird.

453
00:32:04.455 --> 00:32:06.526
My dad is Haida.

454
00:32:07.680 --> 00:32:10.849
They talk about how the raven
was the maker of things.

455
00:32:13.085 --> 00:32:16.425
They say he put the sun
and moon in the sky.

456
00:32:17.429 --> 00:32:20.299
brought fresh water
and fire to the land.

457
00:32:22.535 --> 00:32:26.462
They say he found the first
people inside a giant clamshell.

458
00:32:30.283 --> 00:32:32.250
Bird.

459
00:32:32.672 --> 00:32:34.606
It's just a story.

460
00:32:37.416 --> 00:32:38.683
Made up.

461
00:32:40.660 --> 00:32:42.433
Some things are real.

462
00:32:42.521 --> 00:32:44.819
others are just stories.

463
00:32:48.755 --> 00:32:51.168
This. real.

464
00:32:54.568 --> 00:32:55.701
This.

465
00:32:56.703 --> 00:32:57.903
Real.

466
00:33:02.329 --> 00:33:03.429
Real.

467
00:33:10.057 --> 00:33:11.391
Yes.

468
00:33:11.978 --> 00:33:14.113
You're real.

469
00:33:29.376 --> 00:33:31.010
Okay. so Chris gets attacked.

470
00:33:31.035 --> 00:33:33.236
and your dad calls in the evac?

471
00:33:33.634 --> 00:33:34.836
Yeah.

472
00:33:34.861 --> 00:33:36.735
The military must have been listening.

473
00:33:36.849 --> 00:33:38.968
or CG tipped them off. I don't know.

474
00:33:38.993 --> 00:33:41.028
Did it look like there was
someone in charge?

475
00:33:41.135 --> 00:33:42.368
Yeah.

476
00:33:42.464 --> 00:33:44.932
Okay. so what... what did he look like?

477
00:33:45.226 --> 00:33:47.545
Uh... he was a black dude.

478
00:33:47.601 --> 00:33:49.335
Okay. anything else about him?

479
00:33:49.360 --> 00:33:51.661
I don't know why this is
any of your damn business.

480
00:33:54.061 --> 00:33:56.129
It's like they were
waitin' for us all along.

481
00:33:56.695 --> 00:33:59.334
Like. if it's the military. man.

482
00:34:00.007 --> 00:34:01.272
then they are watching us.

483
00:34:01.297 --> 00:34:02.397
They know stuff about us.

484
00:34:02.422 --> 00:34:03.455
Xander.

485
00:34:03.731 --> 00:34:05.134
They flew off with Chris.

486
00:34:05.159 --> 00:34:06.562
they broke into our place

487
00:34:06.647 --> 00:34:08.448
and took that device.

488
00:34:08.509 --> 00:34:10.399
They are after us. man.

489
00:34:10.799 --> 00:34:12.394
Probably bugged our apartment. too.

490
00:34:12.419 --> 00:34:14.886
- We should do a sweep.
- Yeah. Yes. definitely.

491
00:34:16.891 --> 00:34:19.580
Maybe... maybe... Maybe we. um...

492
00:34:19.667 --> 00:34:22.539
Maybe we post that footage
from the deck. yeah?

493
00:34:22.604 --> 00:34:24.747
Blast it online. just
blow this whole thing up.

494
00:34:24.772 --> 00:34:26.306
It wasn't the military.

495
00:34:28.777 --> 00:34:30.320
What do you mean?

496
00:34:30.452 --> 00:34:31.995
It was me.

497
00:34:32.108 --> 00:34:33.581
I took it.

498
00:34:34.963 --> 00:34:36.364
You?

499
00:34:39.721 --> 00:34:41.322
- What the hell?
- Look. Xander.

500
00:34:41.347 --> 00:34:43.834
I thought I could figure out
what it was. you know.

501
00:34:43.859 --> 00:34:46.007
- I thought it would help Chris.
- That's bullshit!

502
00:34:46.048 --> 00:34:48.328
We should be helping each other.
not fighting each...

503
00:34:49.124 --> 00:34:50.581
Ooh!

504
00:34:53.553 --> 00:34:54.646
Come on!

505
00:34:54.671 --> 00:34:56.859
Hey! Hey. hey. hey. hey! Get off him!

506
00:34:56.972 --> 00:34:58.481
Calvin. seriously.

507
00:34:59.080 --> 00:35:00.981
It's okay. everybody.

508
00:35:02.925 --> 00:35:04.584
I was trying to help.

509
00:35:06.061 --> 00:35:07.809
Look. if you want it.

510
00:35:08.982 --> 00:35:10.712
I'll go get it right now.

511
00:35:12.301 --> 00:35:13.603
Okay.

512
00:35:21.905 --> 00:35:23.116
We need to give it back.

513
00:35:23.141 --> 00:35:24.376
Why? What's happening?

514
00:35:24.401 --> 00:35:25.735
We don't need it anymore.

515
00:35:26.195 --> 00:35:28.402
Ryn. we need to give it back. okay?

516
00:35:28.831 --> 00:35:30.032
No. no. no. no.

517
00:35:30.068 --> 00:35:31.570
We need to give this back.

518
00:35:31.614 --> 00:35:33.182
- Sister!
- This is not your sister.

519
00:35:33.207 --> 00:35:34.540
- Yes!
- Sister is not in here.

520
00:35:34.565 --> 00:35:37.413
We're gonna help you. Friends.

521
00:35:37.554 --> 00:35:39.221
Look. this is Xander.

522
00:35:39.322 --> 00:35:40.690
He can help find your sister.

523
00:35:40.715 --> 00:35:42.850
but we need to give this back to him.

524
00:35:43.339 --> 00:35:45.674
Friend. okay?

525
00:35:49.819 --> 00:35:52.081
Here. Xan. I'm sorry.

526
00:35:52.236 --> 00:35:54.237
Hey.

527
00:35:54.737 --> 00:35:58.026
I was thinking. we should
probably work on the tracking.

528
00:35:58.488 --> 00:36:01.123
See if we can find
where the signal comes from.

529
00:36:05.782 --> 00:36:08.551
Yeah. Yeah. okay. sure. we can try.

530
00:36:10.147 --> 00:36:11.675
What's up. Maddie?

531
00:36:11.820 --> 00:36:12.948
Hey. Xander.

532
00:36:12.973 --> 00:36:14.295
Who's this?

533
00:36:14.872 --> 00:36:17.709
Friend of mine from the
Marine Bio class I'm taking.

534
00:36:17.909 --> 00:36:19.429
While you track that.

535
00:36:19.454 --> 00:36:20.764
I'll try to find out more about the guy

536
00:36:20.789 --> 00:36:22.288
who was on the boat.

537
00:36:22.378 --> 00:36:23.925
I can talk to some of my colleagues

538
00:36:23.973 --> 00:36:25.640
who did some research with the Navy.

539
00:36:25.923 --> 00:36:27.757
see if they know anything.

540
00:36:27.851 --> 00:36:29.668
We're gonna find him. Xan.

541
00:36:39.436 --> 00:36:40.870
In the car.

542
00:37:15.560 --> 00:37:18.592
All right. Okay. so... So we got...

543
00:37:18.817 --> 00:37:21.063
Michael Eaton at PRI.

544
00:37:21.510 --> 00:37:22.544
No. no.

545
00:37:22.578 --> 00:37:25.447
Uh. maybe Amanda Cullen

546
00:37:25.713 --> 00:37:27.816
or Professor Durbin at U-Dub.

547
00:37:28.279 --> 00:37:30.274
We could just send a few emails out.

548
